Features
--------

* **Fieldwork-ready** â€” use the included versions of the LSBQe, AToL, MGT, and digital informed consent forms, or make your own versions.
* **Reproducible** â€” make your research reproducible by simply sharing version information.
* **Extensible** â€” contribute with JSON, Python, HTML and JavaScript or import the backend in your own Python project.
* **Free and open** â€” dual-licensed under the `AGPLv3-or-later <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html>`_ and the `EUPL-1.2+ <https://commission.europa.eu/content/european-union-public-licence_en>`_.
* **Cross-platform** â€” runs on Windows, Linux, and MacOS.

